    "auto_merge": {
        "commit_message": "Essentially to improve older Limited API.\n\nMy reasoning is that using CallMethodObjArgs does two things:\n1. It avoids GetAttr and thus the need to create a bound method.\n2. It allows can internally use vectorcall (at the cost of having to\ndeal with c variadic arguments itself).\n\nI think point 1 is the most important, and this is why I haven't\nbothered to do for function (rather than method) calls.\n\nThe number 5 is a bit arbitrary. It's partly to avoid having to write an\nexcess amount of cases. It's also the number of arguments Python handles\non the stack inside PyObject_CallMethodObjArgs (and above this it\nswitches to heap allocation).",
        "commit_title": "Optimize kwdless callmethod for CYTHON_VECTORCALL=0 (#7707)",
