    "body": "Essentially to improve older Limited API.\r\n\r\nMy reasoning is that using CallMethodObjArgs does two things:\r\n1. It avoids GetAttr and thus the need to create a bound method.\r\n2. It allows can internally use vectorcall (at the cost of having to deal with c variadic arguments itself).\r\n\r\nI think point 1 is the most important, and this is why I haven't bothered to do for function (rather than method) calls.\r\n\r\nThe number 5 is a bit arbitrary. It's partly to avoid having to write an excess amount of cases. It's also the number of arguments Python handles on the stack inside PyObject_CallMethodObjArgs (and above this it switches to heap allocation).",
    "closed_at": "2026-05-24T18:09:20Z",
