                "message": "Optimize kwdless callmethod for CYTHON_VECTORCALL=0\n\nEssentially to improve older Limited API.\n\nMy reasoning is that using CallMethodObjArgs does two things:\n1. It avoids GetAttr and thus the need to create a bound method.\n2. It allows can internally use vectorcall (at the cost of having\n   to deal with c variadic arguments itself).\n\nI think point 1 is the most important, and this is why I haven't\nbothered to do for function (rather than method) calls.\n\nThe number 5 is a bit arbitrary. It's partly to avoid having to\nwrite an excess amount of cases. It's also the number of arguments\nPython handles on the stack inside PyObject_CallMethodObjArgs\n(and above this it switches to heap allocation).",
